# Unipile Gmail Connect Implementation Plan

> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.

**Goal:** Replace direct Gmail OAuth in `nurge connect gmail` with Unipile hosted auth, and replace direct Gmail API sync with Convex-proxied Unipile email fetching — eliminating Google app verification requirements entirely.

**Architecture:** CLI calls Convex HTTP endpoints to get a Unipile hosted auth link, opens it in browser, polls Convex for completion. Sync pulls emails from Convex (which fetches from Unipile) instead of hitting Gmail API directly. The Gmail connector YAML definition and `internal/email/client.go` (direct Gmail API) become dead code.

**Tech Stack:** Go (CLI), Convex (TypeScript HTTP actions/mutations), Unipile REST API

---

## File Structure

| File | Action | Responsibility |
|------|--------|---------------|
| `convex/connect.ts` | Create | HTTP endpoints: `/api/connect-gmail` (get auth link), `/api/connection-status` (poll), `/api/sync-emails` (fetch emails from Convex) |
| `convex/http.ts` | Modify | Register new HTTP routes |
| `convex/unipile.ts` | Modify | Add `triggerBackfill` logic after account callback |
| `convex/webhook.ts` | Modify | Trigger backfill in `unipileAccountCallback` after registration |
| `cmd/connect.go` | Modify | Replace generic connector flow with Convex→Unipile hosted auth |
| `cmd/sync.go` | Modify | Replace direct Gmail API with Convex `/api/sync-emails` |
| `internal/email/client.go` | Delete | No longer needed — CLI never talks to Gmail API |
| `internal/email/sync.go` | Modify | Replace Gmail API sync with Convex-fetched email storage |

---

### Task 1: Convex — Connect & Status Endpoints

**Files:**
- Create: `convex/connect.ts`
- Modify: `convex/http.ts:1-50`

- [ ] **Step 1: Create `convex/connect.ts` with `/api/connect-gmail` endpoint**

This endpoint authenticates the user by token, calls `requestConnectionLink` to get a Unipile hosted auth URL, and returns it.

```typescript
// convex/connect.ts
import { httpAction, internalQuery } from "./_generated/server";
import { api, internal } from "./_generated/api";

// POST /api/connect-gmail — returns Unipile hosted auth URL for Gmail
export const connectGmail = httpAction(async (ctx, request) => {
  try {
    const authHeader = request.headers.get("Authorization");
    if (!authHeader || !authHeader.startsWith("Bearer ")) {
      return new Response(JSON.stringify({ error: "Missing auth token" }), {
        status: 401,
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
      });
    }
    const token = authHeader.slice(7);

    const user = await ctx.runQuery(internal.connect.findUserByToken, { token });
    if (!user) {
      return new Response(JSON.stringify({ error: "Invalid auth token" }), {
        status: 401,
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
      });
    }

    // Check if already connected
    const existing = await ctx.runQuery(internal.connect.findUnipileAccount, {
      userId: user._id,
      provider: "GOOGLE",
    });
    if (existing && existing.status === "connected") {
      return new Response(
        JSON.stringify({ already_connected: true, email: existing.email }),
        { status: 200, headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" } }
      );
    }

    // Get Unipile hosted auth link
    const result = await ctx.runAction(api.unipile.requestConnectionLink, {
      userId: user._id,
      provider: "GOOGLE",
    });

    return new Response(JSON.stringify({ url: result.url }), {
      status: 200,
      headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
    });
  } catch (error: any) {
    return new Response(JSON.stringify({ error: error.message }), {
      status: 500,
      headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
    });
  }
});

// GET /api/connection-status — CLI polls this after opening auth URL
export const connectionStatus = httpAction(async (ctx, request) => {
  try {
    const authHeader = request.headers.get("Authorization");
    if (!authHeader || !authHeader.startsWith("Bearer ")) {
      return new Response(JSON.stringify({ error: "Missing auth token" }), {
        status: 401,
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
      });
    }
    const token = authHeader.slice(7);

    const user = await ctx.runQuery(internal.connect.findUserByToken, { token });
    if (!user) {
      return new Response(JSON.stringify({ error: "Invalid auth token" }), {
        status: 401,
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
      });
    }

    const account = await ctx.runQuery(internal.connect.findUnipileAccount, {
      userId: user._id,
      provider: "GOOGLE",
    });

    if (!account) {
      return new Response(JSON.stringify({ connected: false }), {
        status: 200,
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
      });
    }

    return new Response(
      JSON.stringify({
        connected: account.status === "connected",
        email: account.email || "",
        status: account.status,
      }),
      { status: 200, headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" } }
    );
  } catch (error: any) {
    return new Response(JSON.stringify({ error: error.message }), {
      status: 500,
      headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
    });
  }
});

// --- Internal queries ---

export const findUserByToken = internalQuery({
  args: { token: require("convex/values").v.string() },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    return await ctx.db
      .query("users")
      .withIndex("by_token", (q: any) => q.eq("token", args.token))
      .first();
  },
});

export const findUnipileAccount = internalQuery({
  args: {
    userId: require("convex/values").v.string(),
    provider: require("convex/values").v.string(),
  },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    return await ctx.db
      .query("unipileAccounts")
      .withIndex("by_provider", (q: any) =>
        q.eq("userId", args.userId).eq("provider", args.provider)
      )
      .first();
  },
});
```

- [ ] **Step 2: Add `/api/sync-emails` endpoint to `convex/connect.ts`**

This endpoint returns emails from Convex DB for the authenticated user, with optional cursor-based pagination.

```typescript
// Append to convex/connect.ts

// POST /api/sync-emails — CLI fetches emails from Convex (originally from Unipile backfill)
export const syncEmails = httpAction(async (ctx, request) => {
  try {
    const authHeader = request.headers.get("Authorization");
    if (!authHeader || !authHeader.startsWith("Bearer ")) {
      return new Response(JSON.stringify({ error: "Missing auth token" }), {
        status: 401,
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
      });
    }
    const token = authHeader.slice(7);

    const user = await ctx.runQuery(internal.connect.findUserByToken, { token });
    if (!user) {
      return new Response(JSON.stringify({ error: "Invalid auth token" }), {
        status: 401,
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
      });
    }

    const payload = await request.json().catch(() => ({}));
    const afterVersion = payload.afterVersion ?? 0;

    const emails = await ctx.runQuery(internal.connect.listEmailsAfterVersion, {
      userId: user._id,
      afterVersion,
    });

    return new Response(JSON.stringify({ emails, count: emails.length }), {
      status: 200,
      headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
    });
  } catch (error: any) {
    return new Response(JSON.stringify({ error: error.message }), {
      status: 500,
      headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
    });
  }
});

export const listEmailsAfterVersion = internalQuery({
  args: {
    userId: require("convex/values").v.string(),
    afterVersion: require("convex/values").v.float64(),
  },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    // Get all emails for user with syncVersion > afterVersion
    const emails = await ctx.db
      .query("emails")
      .withIndex("by_user", (q: any) => q.eq("userId", args.userId))
      .collect();
    return emails
      .filter((e: any) => e.syncVersion > args.afterVersion)
      .slice(0, 500); // cap per request
  },
});
```

